                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/328: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McMillin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-09T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Confidential. I was called to Foreign Office this morning. Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs stated that question between Peru and Chile over Tacna and Arica was
                    becoming acute. He intimated that question was even more serious than he could
                    divulge.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
